Usage: analyze_paths_by_bottleneck [-help] {-category <integer> | -incr_delay {worst total}} [-path_num <integer>] [-max_slack <float>] [-min_slack <float>] [-master <string>]

-help                                  # Prints out the command usage
-category <integer>                    # Specifies the number of categories to
                                       # be created for most occurring
                                       # instances. (int, required)
-incr_delay {worst total}              # Specifies that the categories are
                                       # created based on worst incr_delay
                                       # contribution or total incr_delay
                                       # contribution. (enum, required)
-master <string>                       # Specifies that the analysis should be
                                       # performed only for the specified
                                       # master category. (string, optional)
-max_slack <float>                     # Specifies the max slack value of the
                                       # critical paths for bottleneck analysis
                                       # based on incr_delay. (float, optional)
-min_slack <float>                     # Specifies the min slack value of the
                                       # critical paths for bottleneck analysis
                                       # based on incr_delay. (float, optional)
-path_num <integer>                    # Specifies the number of critical paths
                                       # to be analyzed when performing
                                       # bottleneck analysis based on
                                       # incr_delay. (int, optional)